<p>The objective of this chapter is to provide a brief introduction to probability. We start by precisely defining what is meant by randomness and probability. Immediately after, we introduce probability distributions, concentrating on the binomial distribution, which we use to model random noise in our study of coding theory. After defining the basic statistical parameters of mean and standard deviation, we end with an introduction to conditional probability. </p></introduction>

